ote for Trump, and then reiterated that he was =E2=80=9Cleaning toward=E2=
=80=9D voting for him, in an atypical hair-splitting fashion. When I follow=
ed up, asking him for just one good reason why he was seriously considering=
 voting for the former president, he did not reply. I suspect we=E2=80=99ll=
 all know his thinking soon enough, though.
* S.B.F. back in Brooklyn?: Speaking of long, strange trips, Sam Bankman-Fr=
ied is back in Brooklyn, at the Metropolitan Detention Center, according to=
 the Bureau of Prisons. That means in the last few weeks, he was shipped fr=
om Brooklyn to Oklahoma City to Lewisburg, Pennsylvania, before being retur=
ned to the MDC. If anyone can explain this to me, I would love to hear from=
 you.

I suspect Sam is wondering why this happened, too, since he=E2=80=99d asked=
 to stay at MDC until he=E2=80=99s able to file his appeal, which he will p=
robably do sometime this fall. Instead, he
got to take a two-week bus ride=E2=80=94=E2=80=9Cdiesel micro-therapy=E2=80=
=9D perhaps=E2=80=94to the middle of the country, while handcuffed to the s=
eat, and back again to Brooklyn. Kind of kooky, no?

