>wrote about last week</a></u>. There=E2=80=99s also talk of layoffs in New=
 York. But in truth, nobody but the top brass at Sotheby=E2=80=99s knows th=
e extent of the reported restructuring. Even they don=E2=80=99t <i>really</=
i> know because, in the U.K., Sotheby=E2=80=99s must engage in collective c=
onsultation to figure out with employee representatives how to achieve the =
efficiencies that the company needs while minimizing the number of redundan=
cies. That means Sotheby=E2=80=99s has not made decisions yet about individ=
ual roles or total numbers. =E2=80=9CLondon is, and will continue to be, ou=
r largest and most important center for sales, exhibitions, and talent in E=
urope,=E2=80=9D the auction house said in a statement.<br/><br/>Of course, =
there=E2=80=99s nothing unusual about
the seasonal rebalancing of headcount, and Sotheby=E2=80=99s is not alone i=
n that regard. Few people left the auction houses=E2=80=94voluntarily or ot=
herwise=E2=80=94last winter, which is a traditional period for employee tur=
nover. All three major houses are making personnel changes this summer, I=
=E2=80=99m told. And galleries have been holding off cutting staff, too. Th=
ere may have been some hope in the auction business that May would show an =
uptick and justify some of the now-superfluous bodies. Now, it seems, many =
are simply hanging on until after Art Basel next week to make those hard de=
cisions.<br/><br/>This season=E2=80=99s rebalancing will involve new hires =
as well as layoffs, according to Field Recruitment=E2=80=99s <b>Ines de Ser=
oux</b>, who told me that galleries and museums remain in the market for re=
venue producing sales and development staff. =E2=80=9CGalleries are being v=
ery thoughtful about hiring right now=E2=80=94and, more generally speaking,=
 how work is divided between roles,=E2=80=9D added her partner,
<b>Megan ODell</b>. =E2=80=9CWe are very interested in helping our clients =
build sustainable staff structures that are optimal regardless of the marke=
t outlook.=E2=80=9D</li></ul><p></p>
