          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">The great mystery o=
f the Ellison/Cardinale deal, of course, is <i>how</i> <i>much</i> they hav=
e reduced their offer to Shari and sweetened their offer to the non-Redston=
e shareholders of Paramount Global and whether they will lower the asking p=
rice for Skydance. It=E2=80=99s not known yet whether Ellison/RedBird is st=
icking to that $5 billion request, or whether they have reduced their ask s=
lightly in order to further appeal to the special committee and to Shari. N=
or do we know what kind of sweetener Ellison/RedBird have been cooking up f=
or the nonvoting shareholders of Paramount Global, or how much of this new =
money might come out of Shari=E2=80=99s hide. (All of them have their hands=
 out, that=E2=80=99s for sure.) The Paramount stock has inched up roughly 5=
 percent since my partner <b>Dylan Byers</b> <u><a href=3D"https://email.pu=
ck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dQMnVuUVB0blFueEpnRGJ=
SVnJ0ST0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvbmV3c2xldHRlcl9jb250ZW50L25iY3=
Mtc2lyLWNoYXJsZXMtZmFudGFzaWVzLXBhcmFtb3VudC1idXp6LWJlYXN0LWJlbHQtdGlnaHRlb=
mluZy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPURyeStQb3dkZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjg2JTJGMiUyRjI0=
JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9RHJ5K1Bvd2RlcistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODUlMkY4JTJ=
GMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG=
9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2Y=
zYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjkwNjY3NH0/1deb48c6e53b63d990e7bdfa7529=
5e67329db4f5c34e7b27df95f5655100d7f4" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoratio=
n:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">reported</a></u> on Thursday that th=
e special committee was likely to recommend the deal to Shari, which has no=
w happened. But team Ellison/RedBird is keeping quiet about the specifics o=
f their deal, for now.<br/><br/>The most creative part of the Ellison/RedBi=
rd deal is that the newly recapitalized Paramount Global would remain a pub=
lic company, the shareholders of which will be the consortium of Ellison/Re=
dBird/KKR et al. and those existing and future Paramount Global shareholder=
s who decide to take a flier on the new management team and the new structu=
re. And why wouldn=E2=80=99t they stick around at this point to see what th=
is group can do?
The Skydance/RedBird group is hoping that the still-public Paramount Global=
 stock price will one day hit somewhere between $30 and $40 a share under t=
he leadership of Ellison and Shell. Is that crazy? It=E2=80=99s speculative=
, for sure, and it=E2=80=99s quite possible the newly recapitalized stock w=
ill never get there. But some may be persuaded by the specter of a new team=
 after years of woeful mismanagement.<br/><br/>If I were a Paramount shareh=
older, I=E2=80=99d stick around to find out what Ellison/Shell/Zucker can d=
o with this thing, if that=E2=80=99s the way this ends up. After all, they=
=E2=80=99ve pretty much put their money where their mouth is. They don=E2=
=80=99t make money on either their Paramount stock or on their convertible =
preferred until the stock goes up, so at least their economic interests are=
 aligned with yours. But since I=E2=80=99m not a Paramount Global sharehold=
er and never have been, we=E2=80=99ll all just have to wait and see what Sh=
ari decides. (Again, not investment advice=E2=80=A6) <br/><br/>Could
she give us all her answers on Tuesday, as <i>The</i> <i>Wall Street Journa=
l</i> suggested, when Paramount holds its annual shareholder meeting? I wou=
ldn=E2=80=99t hold my breath. Nobody except for Shari seems to know her tim=
ing for a decision, and those that do know ain=E2=80=99t talking. I doubt S=
hari even knows the precise terms of the revised Ellison/RedBird deal yet, =
so an answer by Tuesday seems wildly unrealistic. This is a very big decisi=
on for her, not one to be rushed into because there happens to be an annual=
 shareholders meeting coming up on Zoom. (A spokesman for Shari, <b>Molly</=
b> <b>Morse</b>, at Kekst CNC, declined to elaborate on Shari=E2=80=99s tim=
ing.)<br/></td>
